      "side": 1,
      "message": "Different third party tools use different protocols and want tokens with different scopes. We can conceivably host everything on a single port (and pray URL paths in all protocols are separable), but it will require some non-trivial refactorings to mush everything together (currently each different server is its own package in auth/integration/*).\n\nBut primary reason for this CL is not performance, but removing false impression that it is possible to use e.g. gsutil or git using system context.",
